## Available Scripts

| Script | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `test` | Run tests locally (alias for `test:local`) |
| `test:local` | Run tests against local Selenium |
| `test:remote` | Run tests using Selenoid / remote grid |
| `test:ci` | CI entry point (remote mode; use in pipelines) |
| `test:unit` | Run unit tests for bin helpers |
| `selenoid` | Manage Selenoid instance |

## Environment Variables

Copy [`.env.example`](./.env.example) to `.env` and adjust as needed. Key variables:

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `MODE` | Execution mode: `local` or `remote` |
| `BASE_URL` | Application URL under test |
| `SELENIUM_HUB_HOST` | Selenoid / grid host (remote mode) |
| `SELENIUM_HUB_PORT` | Selenoid / grid port (remote mode) |
| `CHROME` | Number of Chrome instances |
| `FIREFOX` | Number of Firefox instances |
| `SAFARI` | Number of Safari instances |
| `BROWSER_VISIBLE` | Run browsers in visible mode |
| `MAX_INSTANCES` | Maximum number of concurrent instances |

For the full list, see [`.env.example`](./.env.example) and [Test Configuration](./docs/TEST_CONFIGURATION.md).

